From: Jason Germino <jasongermino@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 12 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Makefile: detect target arch from cross-compiler prefix

When cross-compiling, uname -m returns the HOST architecture (x86_64),
not the target. This causes the unix platform block to enable desktop
OpenGL (-lGL, -DHAVE_OPENGL) and set ARCHITECTURE_X64, which then
requires GL/gl.h — absent from the aarch64 cross-compile sysroot.

Check the CC prefix first so that aarch64 cross-builds correctly set
ARCH=aarch64, skipping desktop GL and using the aarch64 JIT path.
---
 Makefile | 8 +++++++-
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/Makefile b/Makefile
--- a/Makefile
+++ b/Makefile
@@ -49,3 +49,9 @@
 ifeq (,$(ARCH))
-   ARCH = $(shell uname -m)
+   ifneq (,$(findstring aarch64,$(CC)))
+      ARCH = aarch64
+   else ifneq (,$(findstring arm,$(CC)))
+      ARCH = arm
+   else
+      ARCH = $(shell uname -m)
+   endif
 endif
